cs.DC, cs.AR, cs.PF, cs.PL, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 

- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper discusses parallel programming and performance on many-core accelerators. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) is also likely as the paper focuses on algorithms for accelerators and proposes new BSP primitives for creating and using streams. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is relevant as the paper discusses predicting running time and identifying bottlenecks in programs targeting many-core accelerators. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper proposes extensions to the BSP model for pseudo-streaming algorithms. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper introduces a new software library called Epiphany BSP for implementing the proposed ideas on the Parallella development board.
